         <div type="translation">
 	<p>A cistern: the meritorious gift of Sulasadatta, the son of Rohiṇimitta, a minter of Cemulla.</p>
         </div>
          
          
          
          
         <div type="commentary">
         <p>A gift by another son of Rohiṇimitta is recorded in <ref target="DHARMA_INSKI00020.xml">KI00020</ref></p>  
         <p>Cemulla, well attested in our corpus, is identified by both B+B and G as modern Chaul, in the Raigan district, approximately 90km south of Kanheri.
         </p>   
         </div>
          
          
          
          
